                <h1>The History of Autism: How Long Has It Been Recognized?</h1>
                <p>Autism has existed throughout history, though it wasn't formally recognized until the mid-20th century. The term "autism" was first introduced in 1943 by Dr. Leo Kanner, but accounts of behaviors resembling autism date back to earlier centuries. Research continues to evolve our understanding of autism's complexities and origins.</p>
